      <prov id="DLM49399" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">68</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">New sections inserted</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>The principal Act is amended by inserting, after <citation jurisdiction="nz">section <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="26350" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 122" atidlm:xmlId="DLM473511" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>122</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="26753" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM473511" atidlm:targetKey="1374603" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM264218" atidlm:targetName="prov 122" atidlm:sourceName="DLM473511" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM263881.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM48977.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Name" atidlm:value="prov" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Amend" atidlm:value="false" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Element_Context" atidlm:value="/act[1]/body[1]/part[1]/prov[67]" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Element_Type" atidlm:value="prov" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Heading" atidlm:value="New sections inserted" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Label" atidlm:value="68" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Legislation_Id" atidlm:value="DLM48971" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Legislation_Number" atidlm:value="140" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Legislation_Title" atidlm:value="Mental Health (Compulsory Assessment and Treatment) Amendment Act 1999" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Legislation_Year" atidlm:value="1999" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Revision_Number" atidlm:value="" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, the following sections:</text>
              <amend>
                <prov id="DLM49600" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">122A</label>
                  <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Certain sections of <citation jurisdiction="nz">Crimes Act 1961</citation> apply to powers to take and retake</heading>
                  <prov.body>
                    <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
                      <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                        <text><citation jurisdiction="nz">Sections 32(1), 38(4)(d), 40(2), 41(4), 41(5), 41(6), 50(4), 51(3), 53, 109(1), 109(4), 110C(2), 111(2), and 113A</citation> contain a power to take or retake a person, a proposed patient, or a patient. In respect of each of these powers, <citation jurisdiction="nz">sections 30, 31, and 34 of the Crimes Act 1961</citation> apply—</text>
                        <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                          <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                            <text>As if the power were a power of arrest; and</text>
                          </para>
                        </label-para>
                        <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                          <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                            <text>With any necessary modifications.</text>
                          </para>
                        </label-para>
                      </para>
                    </subprov>
                  </prov.body>
                </prov>
                <prov id="DLM49601" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">122B</label>
                  <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Use of force</heading>
                  <prov.body>
                    <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
                      <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                        <text>A person exercising a power specified in <citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (2)</citation> may, if he or she is exercising the power in an emergency, use such force as is reasonably necessary in the circumstances.</text>
                      </para>
                    </subprov>
                    <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
                      <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                        <text>The powers are—</text>
                        <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                          <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                            <text>A power to take or retake a person, proposed patient, or patient in any of <citation jurisdiction="nz">sections 32(1), 38(4)(d), 40(2), 41(4), 41(5), 41(6), 50(4), 51(3), 53, 109(1), 109(4), 110C(2), 111(2), or 113A</citation>:</text>
                          </para>
                        </label-para>
                        <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                          <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                            <text>A power to detain a person, proposed patient, or patient in any of <citation jurisdiction="nz">sections 41(3), 41(4), 41(5), 109(4), 110C(2), 111(2), or 113</citation>:</text>
                          </para>
                        </label-para>
                        <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                          <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                            <text>A power to enter premises in either of <citation jurisdiction="nz">sections 41(2) or 110C(1)</citation>.</text>
                          </para>
                        </label-para>
                      </para>
                    </subprov>
                    <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
                      <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                        <text>A person treating a patient to whom <citation jurisdiction="nz">section 59</citation> applies may use such force as is reasonably necessary in the circumstances.</text>
                      </para>
                    </subprov>
                    <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
                      <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                        <text>If force has been used under this section,—</text>
                        <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                          <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                            <text>The circumstances in which the force was used must be recorded as soon as practicable; and</text>
                          </para>
                        </label-para>
                        <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                          <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                            <text>A copy of the record must be given to the Director of Area Mental Health Services as soon as practicable.</text>
                          </para>
                        </label-para>
                      </para>
                    </subprov>
                  </prov.body>
                </prov>
              </amend>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM49602" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">69</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Patient's pocket money</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
